46class Aura;
47//
48// EFFECT HANDLER NOTES
49//
50// in aura handler there should be check for modes:
51// AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL set
52// AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_SEND_FOR_CLIENT_MASK set
53// AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_MASK set - aura is recalculated or is just applied/removed - need to redo all things related to m_amount
54// AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_SEND_FOR_CLIENT_MASK - logical or of above conditions
55// AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_STAT - set when stats are reapplied
56// such checks will speedup trinity change amount/send for client operations
57// because for change amount operation packets will not be send
58// aura effect handlers shouldn't contain any AuraEffect or Aura object modifications
59

547
548AuraEffect::AuraEffect(Aura* base, uint32 effIndex, int32 *baseAmount, Unit* caster) :
549m_base(base), m_spellInfo(base->GetSpellInfo()),
550_effectInfo(base->GetSpellEffectInfo(effIndex)),
551m_baseAmount(baseAmount ? *baseAmount : base->GetSpellEffectInfo(effIndex)->BasePoints),
552m_damage(0), m_critChance(0.0f), m_donePct(1.0f),
553m_spellmod(NULL), m_periodicTimer(0), m_tickNumber(0), m_effIndex(effIndex),
554m_canBeRecalculated(true), m_isPeriodic(false)
555{
556 CalculatePeriodic(caster, true, false);
557
558 m_amount = CalculateAmount(caster);
559
560 CalculateSpellMod();
561}
562
563AuraEffect::~AuraEffect()
564{
565 delete m_spellmod;
566}
567
568void AuraEffect::GetTargetList(std::list<Unit*> & targetList) const
569{
570 Aura::ApplicationMap const & targetMap = GetBase()->GetApplicationMap();
571 // remove all targets which were not added to new list - they no longer deserve area aura
572 for (Aura::ApplicationMap::const_iterator appIter = targetMap.begin(); appIter != targetMap.end(); ++appIter)
573 {
574 if (appIter->second->HasEffect(GetEffIndex()))
575 targetList.push_back(appIter->second->GetTarget());
576 }
577}
578
579void AuraEffect::GetApplicationList(std::list<AuraApplication*> & applicationList) const
580{
581 Aura::ApplicationMap const & targetMap = GetBase()->GetApplicationMap();
582 for (Aura::ApplicationMap::const_iterator appIter = targetMap.begin(); appIter != targetMap.end(); ++appIter)
583 {
584 if (appIter->second->HasEffect(GetEffIndex()))
585 applicationList.push_back(appIter->second);
586 }
587}
588
589int32 AuraEffect::CalculateAmount(Unit* caster)
590{
591 // default amount calculation
592 int32 amount = 0;
593
594 if (!m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR8_MASTERY_SPECIALIZATION) || G3D::fuzzyEq(GetSpellEffectInfo()->BonusCoefficient, 0.0f))
595 amount = GetSpellEffectInfo()->CalcValue(caster, &m_baseAmount, GetBase()->GetOwner()->ToUnit(), nullptr, GetBase()->GetCastItemLevel());
596 else if (caster && caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
597 amount = int32(caster->GetFloatValue(PLAYER_MASTERY) * GetSpellEffectInfo()->BonusCoefficient);
598
599 // check item enchant aura cast
600 if (!amount && caster)
601 {
602 ObjectGuid itemGUID = GetBase()->GetCastItemGUID();
603 if (!itemGUID.IsEmpty())
604 {
605 if (Player* playerCaster = caster->ToPlayer())
606 {
607 if (Item* castItem = playerCaster->GetItemByGuid(itemGUID))
608 {
609 if (castItem->GetItemSuffixFactor())
610 {
611 ItemRandomSuffixEntry const* item_rand_suffix = sItemRandomSuffixStore.LookupEntry(abs(castItem->GetItemRandomPropertyId()));
612 if (item_rand_suffix)
613 {
614 for (int k = 0; k < MAX_ITEM_RANDOM_PROPERTIES; k++)
615 {
616 SpellItemEnchantmentEntry const* pEnchant = sSpellItemEnchantmentStore.LookupEntry(item_rand_suffix->Enchantment[k]);
617 if (pEnchant)
618 {
619 for (int t = 0; t < MAX_ITEM_ENCHANTMENT_EFFECTS; t++)
620 {
621 if (pEnchant->EffectSpellID[t] == m_spellInfo->Id)
622 {
623 amount = uint32((item_rand_suffix->AllocationPct[k] * castItem->GetItemSuffixFactor()) / 10000);
624 break;
625 }
626 }
627 }
628
629 if (amount)
630 break;
631 }
632 }
633 }
634 }
635 }
636 }
637 }
638
639 // custom amount calculations go here
640 switch (GetAuraType())
641 {
642 // crowd control auras
643 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_CONFUSE:
644 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_FEAR:
645 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_STUN:
646 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_ROOT:
647 case SPELL_AURA_TRANSFORM:
648 m_canBeRecalculated = false;
649 if (!m_spellInfo->ProcFlags)
650 break;
651 amount = int32(GetBase()->GetUnitOwner()->CountPctFromMaxHealth(10));
652 if (caster)
653 {
654 // Glyphs increasing damage cap
655 Unit::AuraEffectList const& overrideClassScripts = caster->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_OVERRIDE_CLASS_SCRIPTS);
656 for (Unit::AuraEffectList::const_iterator itr = overrideClassScripts.begin(); itr != overrideClassScripts.end(); ++itr)
657 {
658 if ((*itr)->IsAffectingSpell(m_spellInfo))
659 {
660 // Glyph of Frost nova and similar auras
661 if ((*itr)->GetMiscValue() == 7801)
662 {
663 AddPct(amount, (*itr)->GetAmount());
664 break;
665 }
666 }
667 }
668 }
669 break;
670 case SPELL_AURA_SCHOOL_ABSORB:
671 case SPELL_AURA_MANA_SHIELD:
672 m_canBeRecalculated = false;
673 break;
674 case SPELL_AURA_MOUNTED:
675 {
676 uint32 mountType = uint32(GetMiscValueB());
677 if (MountEntry const* mountEntry = sDB2Manager.GetMount(GetId()))
678 mountType = mountEntry->MountTypeId;
679
680 if (MountCapabilityEntry const* mountCapability = GetBase()->GetUnitOwner()->GetMountCapability(mountType))
681 {
682 amount = mountCapability->ID;
683 m_canBeRecalculated = false;
684 }
685 break;
686 }
687 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_RESISTANCE_EXCLUSIVE:
688 {
689 if (caster)
690 {
691 // if Level <= 70 resist = player level
692 int32 resist = caster->getLevel();
693
694 if (resist > 70 && resist < 81)
695 resist += (resist - 70) * 5;
696 else if (resist > 80)
697 resist += ((resist-70) * 5 + (resist - 80) * 7);
698
699 switch (GetId())
700 {
701 case 20043: // Aspect of the Wild
702 case 8185: // Elemental Resistance
703 case 19891: // Resistance Aura
704 case 79106: // Shadow Protection
705 case 79107: // Shadow Protection
706 amount = resist;
707 break;
708 case 79060: // Mark of the Wild
709 case 79061: // Mark of the Wild
710 case 79062: // Blessing of Kings
711 case 79063: // Blessing of Kings
712 case 90363: // Embrace of the Shale Spider
713 amount = resist / 2;
714 break;
715 }
716 break;
717 }
718 }
719 default:
720 break;
721 }
722
723 GetBase()->CallScriptEffectCalcAmountHandlers(this, amount, m_canBeRecalculated);
724 amount *= GetBase()->GetStackAmount();
725 return amount;
726}
727
728void AuraEffect::CalculatePeriodic(Unit* caster, bool resetPeriodicTimer /*= true*/, bool load /*= false*/)
729{
730 m_period = GetSpellEffectInfo()->ApplyAuraPeriod;
731
732 // prepare periodics
733 switch (GetAuraType())
734 {
735 case SPELL_AURA_OBS_MOD_POWER:
736 // 3 spells have no amplitude set
737 if (!m_period)
738 m_period = 1 * IN_MILLISECONDS;
739 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE:
740 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_HEAL:
741 case SPELL_AURA_OBS_MOD_HEALTH:
742 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL:
743 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_ENERGIZE:
744 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_LEECH:
745 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_HEALTH_FUNNEL:
746 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_MANA_LEECH:
747 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE_PERCENT:
748 case SPELL_AURA_POWER_BURN:
749 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DUMMY:
750 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL_WITH_VALUE:
751 m_isPeriodic = true;
752 break;
753 default:
754 break;
755 }
756
757 GetBase()->CallScriptEffectCalcPeriodicHandlers(this, m_isPeriodic, m_period);
758
759 if (!m_isPeriodic)
760 return;
761
762 Player* modOwner = caster ? caster->GetSpellModOwner() : NULL;
763
764 // Apply casting time mods
765 if (m_period)
766 {
767 // Apply periodic time mod
768 if (modOwner)
769 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(GetId(), SPELLMOD_ACTIVATION_TIME, m_period);
770
771 if (caster)
772 {
773 // Haste modifies periodic time of channeled spells
774 if (m_spellInfo->IsChanneled())
775 {
776 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR5_HASTE_AFFECT_DURATION))
777 caster->ModSpellCastTime(m_spellInfo, m_period);
778 }
779 else if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR5_HASTE_AFFECT_DURATION))
780 m_period = int32(m_period * caster->GetFloatValue(UNIT_MOD_CAST_SPEED));
781 }
782 }
783
784 if (load) // aura loaded from db
785 {
786 m_tickNumber = m_period ? GetBase()->GetDuration() / m_period : 0;
787 m_periodicTimer = m_period ? GetBase()->GetDuration() % m_period : 0;
788 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR5_START_PERIODIC_AT_APPLY))
789 ++m_tickNumber;
790 }
791 else // aura just created or reapplied
792 {
793 m_tickNumber = 0;
794 // reset periodic timer on aura create or on reapply when aura isn't dot
795 // possibly we should not reset periodic timers only when aura is triggered by proc
796 // or maybe there's a spell attribute somewhere
797 if (resetPeriodicTimer)
798 {
799 m_periodicTimer = 0;
800 // Start periodic on next tick or at aura apply
801 if (m_period && !m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR5_START_PERIODIC_AT_APPLY))
802 m_periodicTimer += m_period;
803 }
804 }
805}
806
807void AuraEffect::CalculateSpellMod()
808{
809 switch (GetAuraType())
810 {
811 case SPELL_AURA_ADD_FLAT_MODIFIER:
812 case SPELL_AURA_ADD_PCT_MODIFIER:
813 if (!m_spellmod)
814 {
815 m_spellmod = new SpellModifier(GetBase());
816 m_spellmod->op = SpellModOp(GetMiscValue());
817
818 m_spellmod->type = SpellModType(uint32(GetAuraType())); // SpellModType value == spell aura types
819 m_spellmod->spellId = GetId();
820 m_spellmod->mask = GetSpellEffectInfo()->SpellClassMask;
821 m_spellmod->charges = GetBase()->GetCharges();
822 }
823 m_spellmod->value = GetAmount();
824 break;
825 default:
826 break;
827 }
828 GetBase()->CallScriptEffectCalcSpellModHandlers(this, m_spellmod);
829}
830
831void AuraEffect::ChangeAmount(int32 newAmount, bool mark, bool onStackOrReapply)
832{
833 // Reapply if amount change
834 uint8 handleMask = 0;
835 if (newAmount != GetAmount())
836 handleMask |= AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT;
837 if (onStackOrReapply)
838 handleMask |= AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAPPLY;
839
840 if (!handleMask)
841 return;
842
843 std::list<AuraApplication*> effectApplications;
844 GetApplicationList(effectApplications);
845
846 for (std::list<AuraApplication*>::const_iterator apptItr = effectApplications.begin(); apptItr != effectApplications.end(); ++apptItr)
847 if ((*apptItr)->HasEffect(GetEffIndex()))
848 HandleEffect(*apptItr, handleMask, false);
849
850 if (handleMask & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT)
851 {
852 if (!mark)
853 m_amount = newAmount;
854 else
855 SetAmount(newAmount);
856 CalculateSpellMod();
857 }
858
859 for (std::list<AuraApplication*>::const_iterator apptItr = effectApplications.begin(); apptItr != effectApplications.end(); ++apptItr)
860 if ((*apptItr)->HasEffect(GetEffIndex()))
861 HandleEffect(*apptItr, handleMask, true);
862}
863
864void AuraEffect::HandleEffect(AuraApplication * aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply)
865{
866 // check if call is correct, we really don't want using bitmasks here (with 1 exception)
867 ASSERT(mode == AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL
868 || mode == AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_SEND_FOR_CLIENT
869 || mode == AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT
870 || mode == AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_STAT
871 || mode == AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_SKILL
872 || mode == AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAPPLY
873 || mode == (AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT | AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAPPLY));
874
875 // register/unregister effect in lists in case of real AuraEffect apply/remove
876 // registration/unregistration is done always before real effect handling (some effect handlers code is depending on this)
877 if (mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL)
878 aurApp->GetTarget()->_RegisterAuraEffect(this, apply);
879
880 // real aura apply/remove, handle modifier
881 if (mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_MASK)
882 ApplySpellMod(aurApp->GetTarget(), apply);
883
884 // call scripts helping/replacing effect handlers
885 bool prevented = false;
886 if (apply)
887 prevented = GetBase()->CallScriptEffectApplyHandlers(this, aurApp, (AuraEffectHandleModes)mode);
888 else
889 prevented = GetBase()->CallScriptEffectRemoveHandlers(this, aurApp, (AuraEffectHandleModes)mode);
890
891 // check if script events have removed the aura or if default effect prevention was requested
892 if ((apply && aurApp->GetRemoveMode()) || prevented)
893 return;
894
895 (*this.*AuraEffectHandler[GetAuraType()])(aurApp, mode, apply);
896
897 // check if script events have removed the aura or if default effect prevention was requested
898 if (apply && aurApp->GetRemoveMode())
899 return;
900
901 // call scripts triggering additional events after apply/remove
902 if (apply)
903 GetBase()->CallScriptAfterEffectApplyHandlers(this, aurApp, (AuraEffectHandleModes)mode);
904 else
905 GetBase()->CallScriptAfterEffectRemoveHandlers(this, aurApp, (AuraEffectHandleModes)mode);
906}
907
908void AuraEffect::HandleEffect(Unit* target, uint8 mode, bool apply)
909{
910 AuraApplication* aurApp = GetBase()->GetApplicationOfTarget(target->GetGUID());
911 ASSERT(aurApp);
912 HandleEffect(aurApp, mode, apply);
913}
914
915void AuraEffect::ApplySpellMod(Unit* target, bool apply)
916{
917 if (!m_spellmod || target->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
918 return;
919
920 target->ToPlayer()->AddSpellMod(m_spellmod, apply);
921
922 // Auras with charges do not mod amount of passive auras
923 if (GetBase()->IsUsingCharges())
924 return;
925 // reapply some passive spells after add/remove related spellmods
926 // Warning: it is a dead loop if 2 auras each other amount-shouldn't happen
927 switch (GetMiscValue())
928 {
929 case SPELLMOD_ALL_EFFECTS:
930 case SPELLMOD_EFFECT1:
931 case SPELLMOD_EFFECT2:
932 case SPELLMOD_EFFECT3:
933 case SPELLMOD_EFFECT4:
934 case SPELLMOD_EFFECT5:
935 {
936 ObjectGuid guid = target->GetGUID();
937 Unit::AuraApplicationMap & auras = target->GetAppliedAuras();
938 for (Unit::AuraApplicationMap::iterator iter = auras.begin(); iter != auras.end(); ++iter)
939 {
940 Aura* aura = iter->second->GetBase();
941 // only passive and permament auras-active auras should have amount set on spellcast and not be affected
942 // if aura is cast by others, it will not be affected
943 if ((aura->IsPassive() || aura->IsPermanent()) && aura->GetCasterGUID() == guid && aura->GetSpellInfo()->IsAffectedBySpellMod(m_spellmod))
944 {
945 if (GetMiscValue() == SPELLMOD_ALL_EFFECTS)
946 {
947 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
948 {
949 if (AuraEffect* aurEff = aura->GetEffect(i))
950 aurEff->RecalculateAmount();
951 }
952 }
953 else if (GetMiscValue() == SPELLMOD_EFFECT1)
954 {
955 if (AuraEffect* aurEff = aura->GetEffect(0))
956 aurEff->RecalculateAmount();
957 }
958 else if (GetMiscValue() == SPELLMOD_EFFECT2)
959 {
960 if (AuraEffect* aurEff = aura->GetEffect(1))
961 aurEff->RecalculateAmount();
962 }
963 else if (GetMiscValue() == SPELLMOD_EFFECT3)
964 {
965 if (AuraEffect* aurEff = aura->GetEffect(2))
966 aurEff->RecalculateAmount();
967 }
968 else if (GetMiscValue() == SPELLMOD_EFFECT4)
969 {
970 if (AuraEffect* aurEff = aura->GetEffect(3))
971 aurEff->RecalculateAmount();
972 }
973 else if (GetMiscValue() == SPELLMOD_EFFECT5)
974 {
975 if (AuraEffect* aurEff = aura->GetEffect(4))
976 aurEff->RecalculateAmount();
977 }
978 }
979 }
980 }
981 default:
982 break;
983 }
984}
985
986void AuraEffect::Update(uint32 diff, Unit* caster)
987{
988 if (m_isPeriodic && (GetBase()->GetDuration() >=0 || GetBase()->IsPassive() || GetBase()->IsPermanent()))
989 {
990 if (m_periodicTimer > int32(diff))
991 m_periodicTimer -= diff;
992 else // tick also at m_periodicTimer == 0 to prevent lost last tick in case max m_duration == (max m_periodicTimer)*N
993 {
994 ++m_tickNumber;
995
996 // update before tick (aura can be removed in TriggerSpell or PeriodicTick calls)
997 m_periodicTimer += m_period - diff;
998 UpdatePeriodic(caster);
999
1000 std::list<AuraApplication*> effectApplications;
1001 GetApplicationList(effectApplications);
1002 // tick on targets of effects
1003 for (std::list<AuraApplication*>::const_iterator apptItr = effectApplications.begin(); apptItr != effectApplications.end(); ++apptItr)
1004 if ((*apptItr)->HasEffect(GetEffIndex()))
1005 PeriodicTick(*apptItr, caster);
1006 }
1007 }
1008}
1009
1010void AuraEffect::UpdatePeriodic(Unit* caster)
1011{
1012 switch (GetAuraType())
1013 {
1014 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DUMMY:
1015 switch (GetSpellInfo()->SpellFamilyName)
1016 {
1017 case SPELLFAMILY_GENERIC:
1018 switch (GetId())
1019 {
1020 // Drink
1021 case 430:
1022 case 431:
1023 case 432:
1024 case 1133:
1025 case 1135:
1026 case 1137:
1027 case 10250:
1028 case 22734:
1029 case 27089:
1030 case 34291:
1031 case 43182:
1032 case 43183:
1033 case 46755:
1034 case 49472: // Drink Coffee
1035 case 57073:
1036 case 61830:
1037 case 69176:
1038 case 72623:
1039 case 80166:
1040 case 80167:
1041 case 87958:
1042 case 87959:
1043 case 92736:
1044 case 92797:
1045 case 92800:
1046 case 92803:
1047 if (!caster || caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
1048 return;
1049 // Get SPELL_AURA_MOD_POWER_REGEN aura from spell
1050 if (AuraEffect* aurEff = GetBase()->GetEffect(0))
1051 {
1052 if (aurEff->GetAuraType() != SPELL_AURA_MOD_POWER_REGEN)
1053 {
1054 m_isPeriodic = false;
1055 TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "Aura %d structure has been changed - first aura is no longer SPELL_AURA_MOD_POWER_REGEN", GetId());
1056 }
1057 else
1058 {
1059 // default case - not in arena
1060 if (!caster->ToPlayer()->InArena())
1061 {
1062 aurEff->ChangeAmount(GetAmount());
1063 m_isPeriodic = false;
1064 }
1065 else
1066 {
1067 // **********************************************
1068 // This feature uses only in arenas
1069 // **********************************************
1070 // Here need increase mana regen per tick (6 second rule)
1071 // on 0 tick - 0 (handled in 2 second)
1072 // on 1 tick - 166% (handled in 4 second)
1073 // on 2 tick - 133% (handled in 6 second)
1074
1075 // Apply bonus for 1 - 4 tick
1076 switch (m_tickNumber)
1077 {
1078 case 1: // 0%
1079 aurEff->ChangeAmount(0);
1080 break;
1081 case 2: // 166%
1082 aurEff->ChangeAmount(GetAmount() * 5 / 3);
1083 break;
1084 case 3: // 133%
1085 aurEff->ChangeAmount(GetAmount() * 4 / 3);
1086 break;
1087 default: // 100% - normal regen
1088 aurEff->ChangeAmount(GetAmount());
1089 // No need to update after 4th tick
1090 m_isPeriodic = false;
1091 break;
1092 }
1093 }
1094 }
1095 }
1096 break;
1097 case 58549: // Tenacity
1098 case 59911: // Tenacity (vehicle)
1099 GetBase()->RefreshDuration();
1100 break;
1101 case 66823: case 67618: case 67619: case 67620: // Paralytic Toxin
1102 // Get 0 effect aura
1103 if (AuraEffect* slow = GetBase()->GetEffect(0))
1104 {
1105 int32 newAmount = slow->GetAmount() - 10;
1106 if (newAmount < -100)
1107 newAmount = -100;
1108 slow->ChangeAmount(newAmount);
1109 }
1110 break;
1111 default:
1112 break;
1113 }
1114 break;
1115 case SPELLFAMILY_MAGE:
1116 if (GetId() == 55342)// Mirror Image
1117 m_isPeriodic = false;
1118 break;
1119 case SPELLFAMILY_DEATHKNIGHT:
1120 // Chains of Ice
1121 if (GetSpellInfo()->SpellFamilyFlags[1] & 0x00004000)
1122 {
1123 // Get 0 effect aura
1124 if (AuraEffect* slow = GetBase()->GetEffect(0))
1125 {
1126 int32 newAmount = slow->GetAmount() + GetAmount();
1127 if (newAmount > 0)
1128 newAmount = 0;
1129 slow->ChangeAmount(newAmount);
1130 }
1131 return;
1132 }
1133 break;
1134 default:
1135 break;
1136 }
1137 default:
1138 break;
1139 }
1140 GetBase()->CallScriptEffectUpdatePeriodicHandlers(this);
1141}
1142
1143bool AuraEffect::CanPeriodicTickCrit(Unit const* caster) const
1144{
1145 ASSERT(caster);
1146
1147 return caster->HasAuraTypeWithAffectMask(SPELL_AURA_ABILITY_PERIODIC_CRIT, m_spellInfo);
1148}
1149
1150bool AuraEffect::IsAffectingSpell(SpellInfo const* spell) const
1151{
1152 if (!spell)
1153 return false;
1154 // Check family name
1155 if (spell->SpellFamilyName != m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName)
1156 return false;
1157
1158 // Check EffectClassMask
1159 if (GetSpellEffectInfo()->SpellClassMask & spell->SpellFamilyFlags)
1160 return true;
1161 return false;
1162}
1163
1164void AuraEffect::SendTickImmune(Unit* target, Unit* caster) const
1165{
1166 if (caster)
1167 caster->SendSpellDamageImmune(target, m_spellInfo->Id, true);
1168}
1169
1170void AuraEffect::PeriodicTick(AuraApplication * aurApp, Unit* caster) const
1171{
1172 bool prevented = GetBase()->CallScriptEffectPeriodicHandlers(this, aurApp);
1173 if (prevented)
1174 return;
1175
1176 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
1177
1178 switch (GetAuraType())
1179 {
1180 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DUMMY:
1181 HandlePeriodicDummyAuraTick(target, caster);
1182 break;
1183 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL:
1184 HandlePeriodicTriggerSpellAuraTick(target, caster);
1185 break;
1186 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL_WITH_VALUE:
1187 HandlePeriodicTriggerSpellWithValueAuraTick(target, caster);
1188 break;
1189 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE:
1190 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE_PERCENT:
1191 HandlePeriodicDamageAurasTick(target, caster);
1192 break;
1193 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_LEECH:
1194 HandlePeriodicHealthLeechAuraTick(target, caster);
1195 break;
1196 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_HEALTH_FUNNEL:
1197 HandlePeriodicHealthFunnelAuraTick(target, caster);
1198 break;
1199 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_HEAL:
1200 case SPELL_AURA_OBS_MOD_HEALTH:
1201 HandlePeriodicHealAurasTick(target, caster);
1202 break;
1203 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_MANA_LEECH:
1204 HandlePeriodicManaLeechAuraTick(target, caster);
1205 break;
1206 case SPELL_AURA_OBS_MOD_POWER:
1207 HandleObsModPowerAuraTick(target, caster);
1208 break;
1209 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_ENERGIZE:
1210 HandlePeriodicEnergizeAuraTick(target, caster);
1211 break;
1212 case SPELL_AURA_POWER_BURN:
1213 HandlePeriodicPowerBurnAuraTick(target, caster);
1214 break;
1215 default:
1216 break;
1217 }
1218}
1219
1220void AuraEffect::HandleProc(AuraApplication* aurApp, ProcEventInfo& eventInfo)
1221{
1222 bool prevented = GetBase()->CallScriptEffectProcHandlers(this, aurApp, eventInfo);
1223 if (prevented)
1224 return;
1225
1226 switch (GetAuraType())
1227 {
1228 case SPELL_AURA_PROC_TRIGGER_SPELL:
1229 HandleProcTriggerSpellAuraProc(aurApp, eventInfo);
1230 break;
1231 case SPELL_AURA_PROC_TRIGGER_SPELL_WITH_VALUE:
1232 HandleProcTriggerSpellWithValueAuraProc(aurApp, eventInfo);
1233 break;
1234 case SPELL_AURA_PROC_TRIGGER_DAMAGE:
1235 HandleProcTriggerDamageAuraProc(aurApp, eventInfo);
1236 break;
1237 case SPELL_AURA_RAID_PROC_FROM_CHARGE:
1238 HandleRaidProcFromChargeAuraProc(aurApp, eventInfo);
1239 break;
1240 case SPELL_AURA_RAID_PROC_FROM_CHARGE_WITH_VALUE:
1241 HandleRaidProcFromChargeWithValueAuraProc(aurApp, eventInfo);
1242 break;
1243 case SPELL_AURA_PROC_ON_POWER_AMOUNT:
1244 HandleProcTriggerSpellOnPowerAmountAuraProc(aurApp, eventInfo);
1245 break;
1246 default:
1247 break;
1248 }
1249
1250 GetBase()->CallScriptAfterEffectProcHandlers(this, aurApp, eventInfo);
1251}
1252
1253void AuraEffect::CleanupTriggeredSpells(Unit* target)
1254{
1255 uint32 tSpellId = GetSpellEffectInfo()->TriggerSpell;
1256 if (!tSpellId)
1257 return;
1258
1259 SpellInfo const* tProto = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(tSpellId);
1260 if (!tProto)
1261 return;
1262
1263 if (tProto->GetDuration() != -1)
1264 return;
1265
1266 // needed for spell 43680, maybe others
1267 /// @todo is there a spell flag, which can solve this in a more sophisticated way?
1268 if (GetSpellEffectInfo()->ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL &&
1269 uint32(m_spellInfo->GetDuration()) == GetSpellEffectInfo()->ApplyAuraPeriod)
1270 return;
1271
1272 target->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(tSpellId, GetCasterGUID());
1273}
1274
1275void AuraEffect::HandleShapeshiftBoosts(Unit* target, bool apply) const
1276{
1277 uint32 spellId = 0;
1278 uint32 spellId2 = 0;
1279
1280 switch (GetMiscValue())
1281 {
1282 case FORM_CAT:
1283 spellId = 3025;
1284 break;
1285 case FORM_TREE:
1286 spellId = 34123;
1287 break;
1288 case FORM_TRAVEL:
1289 spellId = 5419;
1290 break;
1291 case FORM_AQUA:
1292 spellId = 5421;
1293 break;
1294 case FORM_BEAR:
1295 spellId = 1178;
1296 spellId2 = 21178;
1297 break;
1298 case FORM_BATTLESTANCE:
1299 spellId = 21156;
1300 break;
1301 case FORM_DEFENSIVESTANCE:
1302 spellId = 7376;
1303 break;
1304 case FORM_BERSERKERSTANCE:
1305 spellId = 7381;
1306 break;
1307 case FORM_MOONKIN:
1308 spellId = 24905;
1309 spellId2 = 24907;
1310 break;
1311 case FORM_FLIGHT:
1312 spellId = 33948;
1313 spellId2 = 34764;
1314 break;
1315 case FORM_FLIGHT_EPIC:
1316 spellId = 40122;
1317 spellId2 = 40121;
1318 break;
1319 case FORM_METAMORPHOSIS:
1320 spellId = 54817;
1321 spellId2 = 54879;
1322 break;
1323 case FORM_SPIRITOFREDEMPTION:
1324 spellId = 27792;
1325 spellId2 = 27795; // must be second, this important at aura remove to prevent to early iterator invalidation.
1326 break;
1327 case FORM_SHADOW:
1328 spellId = 49868;
1329 break;
1330 case FORM_GHOSTWOLF:
1331 spellId = 67116;
1332 break;
1333 case FORM_GHOUL:
1334 case FORM_AMBIENT:
1335 case FORM_STEALTH:
1336 case FORM_CREATURECAT:
1337 case FORM_CREATUREBEAR:
1338 break;
1339 default:
1340 break;
1341 }
1342
1343 if (apply)
1344 {
1345 if (spellId)
1346 target->CastSpell(target, spellId, true, NULL, this);
1347
1348 if (spellId2)
1349 target->CastSpell(target, spellId2, true, NULL, this);
1350
1351 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1352 {
1353 Player* plrTarget = target->ToPlayer();
1354
1355 PlayerSpellMap const& sp_list = plrTarget->GetSpellMap();
1356 for (PlayerSpellMap::const_iterator itr = sp_list.begin(); itr != sp_list.end(); ++itr)
1357 {
1358 if (itr->second->state == PLAYERSPELL_REMOVED || itr->second->disabled)
1359 continue;
1360
1361 if (itr->first == spellId || itr->first == spellId2)
1362 continue;
1363
1364 SpellInfo const* spellInfo = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(itr->first);
1365 if (!spellInfo || !(spellInfo->Attributes & (SPELL_ATTR0_PASSIVE | SPELL_ATTR0_HIDDEN_CLIENTSIDE)))
1366 continue;
1367
1368 if ((spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR8_MASTERY_SPECIALIZATION)) && !plrTarget->IsCurrentSpecMasterySpell(spellInfo))
1369 continue;
1370
1371 if (spellInfo->Stances & (UI64LIT(1) << (GetMiscValue() - 1)))
1372 target->CastSpell(target, itr->first, true, NULL, this);
1373 }
1374
1375 // Also do it for Glyphs
1376 for (uint32 i = 0; i < MAX_GLYPH_SLOT_INDEX; ++i)
1377 {
1378 if (uint32 glyphId = plrTarget->GetGlyph(plrTarget->GetActiveTalentGroup(), i))
1379 {
1380 if (GlyphPropertiesEntry const* glyph = sGlyphPropertiesStore.LookupEntry(glyphId))
1381 {
1382 SpellInfo const* spellInfo = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(glyph->SpellID);
1383 if (!spellInfo || !(spellInfo->Attributes & (SPELL_ATTR0_PASSIVE | SPELL_ATTR0_HIDDEN_CLIENTSIDE)))
1384 continue;
1385
1386 if (spellInfo->Stances & (UI64LIT(1) << (GetMiscValue() - 1)))
1387 target->CastSpell(target, glyph->SpellID, true, NULL, this);
1388 }
1389 }
1390 }
1391
1392 // Leader of the Pack
1393 if (plrTarget->HasSpell(17007))
1394 {
1395 SpellInfo const* spellInfo = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(24932);
1396 if (spellInfo && spellInfo->Stances & (UI64LIT(1) << (GetMiscValue() -1)))
1397 target->CastSpell(target, 24932, true, NULL, this);
1398 }
1399
1400 switch (GetMiscValue())
1401 {
1402 case FORM_CAT:
1403 // Savage Roar
1404 if (target->GetAuraEffect(SPELL_AURA_DUMMY, SPELLFAMILY_DRUID, flag128(0, 0x10000000, 0)))
1405 target->CastSpell(target, 62071, true);
1406 // Nurturing Instinct
1407 if (AuraEffect const* aurEff = target->GetAuraEffect(SPELL_AURA_MOD_SPELL_HEALING_OF_STAT_PERCENT, SPELLFAMILY_DRUID, 2254, EFFECT_0))
1408 {
1409 uint32 spellId3 = 0;
1410 switch (aurEff->GetId())
1411 {
1412 case 33872:
1413 spellId3 = 47179;
1414 break;
1415 case 33873:
1416 spellId3 = 47180;
1417 break;
1418 }
1419 target->CastSpell(target, spellId3, true, NULL, this);
1420 }
1421 // Master Shapeshifter - Cat
1422 if (AuraEffect const* aurEff = target->GetAuraEffect(SPELL_AURA_MOD_HEALING_DONE_PERCENT, SPELLFAMILY_GENERIC, 2851, EFFECT_0))
1423 {
1424 int32 bp = aurEff->GetAmount();
1425 target->CastCustomSpell(target, 48420, &bp, NULL, NULL, true);
1426 }
1427 break;
1428 case FORM_BEAR:
1429 // Master Shapeshifter - Bear
1430 if (AuraEffect const* aurEff = target->GetAuraEffect(SPELL_AURA_MOD_HEALING_DONE_PERCENT, SPELLFAMILY_GENERIC, 2851, EFFECT_0))
1431 {
1432 int32 bp = aurEff->GetAmount();
1433 target->CastCustomSpell(target, 48418, &bp, NULL, NULL, true);
1434 }
1435 break;
1436 case FORM_MOONKIN:
1437 // Master Shapeshifter - Moonkin
1438 if (AuraEffect const* aurEff = target->GetAuraEffect(SPELL_AURA_MOD_HEALING_DONE_PERCENT, SPELLFAMILY_GENERIC, 2851, EFFECT_0))
1439 {
1440 int32 bp = aurEff->GetAmount();
1441 target->CastCustomSpell(target, 48421, &bp, NULL, NULL, true);
1442 }
1443 break;
1444 default:
1445 break;
1446 }
1447 }
1448 }
1449 else
1450 {
1451 if (spellId)
1452 target->RemoveOwnedAura(spellId, target->GetGUID());
1453 if (spellId2)
1454 target->RemoveOwnedAura(spellId2, target->GetGUID());
1455
1456 Unit::AuraEffectList const& shapeshifts = target->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_SHAPESHIFT);
1457 AuraEffect* newAura = NULL;
1458 // Iterate through all the shapeshift auras that the target has, if there is another aura with SPELL_AURA_MOD_SHAPESHIFT, then this aura is being removed due to that one being applied
1459 for (Unit::AuraEffectList::const_iterator itr = shapeshifts.begin(); itr != shapeshifts.end(); ++itr)
1460 {
1461 if ((*itr) != this)
1462 {
1463 newAura = *itr;
1464 break;
1465 }
1466 }
1467
1468 Unit::AuraApplicationMap& tAuras = target->GetAppliedAuras();
1469 for (Unit::AuraApplicationMap::iterator itr = tAuras.begin(); itr != tAuras.end();)
1470 {
1471 // Use the new aura to see on what stance the target will be
1472 uint64 newStance = newAura ? (UI64LIT(1) << (newAura->GetMiscValue() - 1)) : 0;
1473
1474 // If the stances are not compatible with the spell, remove it
1475 if (itr->second->GetBase()->IsRemovedOnShapeLost(target) && !(itr->second->GetBase()->GetSpellInfo()->Stances & newStance))
1476 target->RemoveAura(itr);
1477 else
1478 ++itr;
1479 }
1480 }
1481}
1482
1483/*********************************************************/
1484/*** AURA EFFECT HANDLERS ***/
1485/*********************************************************/

1489/**************************************/
1490
1491void AuraEffect::HandleModInvisibilityDetect(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
1492{
1493 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_MASK))
1494 return;
1495
1496 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
1497 InvisibilityType type = InvisibilityType(GetMiscValue());
1498
1499 if (apply)
1500 {
1501 target->m_invisibilityDetect.AddFlag(type);
1502 target->m_invisibilityDetect.AddValue(type, GetAmount());
1503 }
1504 else
1505 {
1506 if (!target->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_INVISIBILITY_DETECT))
1507 target->m_invisibilityDetect.DelFlag(type);
1508
1509 target->m_invisibilityDetect.AddValue(type, -GetAmount());
1510 }
1511
1512 // call functions which may have additional effects after chainging state of unit
1513 target->UpdateObjectVisibility();
1514}
1515
1516void AuraEffect::HandleModInvisibility(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
1517{
1518 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_SEND_FOR_CLIENT_MASK))
1519 return;
1520
1521 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
1522 InvisibilityType type = InvisibilityType(GetMiscValue());
1523
1524 if (apply)
1525 {
1526 // apply glow vision
1527 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1528 target->SetByteFlag(PLAYER_FIELD_BYTES2, PLAYER_FIELD_BYTES_2_OFFSET_AURA_VISION, PLAYER_FIELD_BYTE2_INVISIBILITY_GLOW);
1529
1530 target->m_invisibility.AddFlag(type);
1531 target->m_invisibility.AddValue(type, GetAmount());
1532 }
1533 else
1534 {
1535 if (!target->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_INVISIBILITY))
1536 {
1537 // if not have different invisibility auras.
1538 // remove glow vision
1539 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1540 target->RemoveByteFlag(PLAYER_FIELD_BYTES2, PLAYER_FIELD_BYTES_2_OFFSET_AURA_VISION, PLAYER_FIELD_BYTE2_INVISIBILITY_GLOW);
1541
1542 target->m_invisibility.DelFlag(type);
1543 }
1544 else
1545 {
1546 bool found = false;
1547 Unit::AuraEffectList const& invisAuras = target->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_INVISIBILITY);
1548 for (Unit::AuraEffectList::const_iterator i = invisAuras.begin(); i != invisAuras.end(); ++i)
1549 {
1550 if (GetMiscValue() == (*i)->GetMiscValue())
1551 {
1552 found = true;
1553 break;
1554 }
1555 }
1556 if (!found)
1557 target->m_invisibility.DelFlag(type);
1558 }
1559
1560 target->m_invisibility.AddValue(type, -GetAmount());
1561 }
1562
1563 // call functions which may have additional effects after chainging state of unit
1564 if (apply && (mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
1565 {
1566 // drop flag at invisibiliy in bg
1567 target->RemoveAurasWithInterruptFlags(AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_IMMUNE_OR_LOST_SELECTION);
1568 }
1569 target->UpdateObjectVisibility();
1570}
1571
1572void AuraEffect::HandleModStealthDetect(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
1573{
1574 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_MASK))

1579
1580 if (apply)
1581 {
1582 target->m_stealthDetect.AddFlag(type);
1583 target->m_stealthDetect.AddValue(type, GetAmount());
1584 }
1585 else
1586 {
1587 if (!target->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_STEALTH_DETECT))
1588 target->m_stealthDetect.DelFlag(type);
1589
1590 target->m_stealthDetect.AddValue(type, -GetAmount());
1591 }
1592
1593 // call functions which may have additional effects after chainging state of unit
1594 target->UpdateObjectVisibility();
1595}
1596
1597void AuraEffect::HandleModStealth(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
1598{
1599 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_SEND_FOR_CLIENT_MASK))
1600 return;
1601
1602 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
1603 StealthType type = StealthType(GetMiscValue());
1604
1605 if (apply)
1606 {
1607 target->m_stealth.AddFlag(type);
1608 target->m_stealth.AddValue(type, GetAmount());
1609
1610 target->SetStandFlags(UNIT_STAND_FLAGS_CREEP);
1611 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1612 target->SetByteFlag(PLAYER_FIELD_BYTES2, PLAYER_FIELD_BYTES_2_OFFSET_AURA_VISION, PLAYER_FIELD_BYTE2_STEALTH);
1613 }
1614 else
1615 {
1616 target->m_stealth.AddValue(type, -GetAmount());
1617
1618 if (!target->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_STEALTH)) // if last SPELL_AURA_MOD_STEALTH
1619 {
1620 target->m_stealth.DelFlag(type);
1621
1622 target->RemoveStandFlags(UNIT_STAND_FLAGS_CREEP);
1623 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1624 target->RemoveByteFlag(PLAYER_FIELD_BYTES2, PLAYER_FIELD_BYTES_2_OFFSET_AURA_VISION, PLAYER_FIELD_BYTE2_STEALTH);
1625 }
1626 }
1627
1628 // call functions which may have additional effects after chainging state of unit
1629 if (apply && (mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
1630 {
1631 // drop flag at stealth in bg
1632 target->RemoveAurasWithInterruptFlags(AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_IMMUNE_OR_LOST_SELECTION);
1633 }
1634 target->UpdateObjectVisibility();
1635}
1636
1637void AuraEffect::HandleModStealthLevel(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
1638{
1639 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_MASK))
1640 return;
1641
1642 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
1643 StealthType type = StealthType(GetMiscValue());
1644
1645 if (apply)
1646 target->m_stealth.AddValue(type, GetAmount());
1647 else
1648 target->m_stealth.AddValue(type, -GetAmount());
1649
1650 // call functions which may have additional effects after chainging state of unit
1651 target->UpdateObjectVisibility();
1652}
1653
1654void AuraEffect::HandleSpiritOfRedemption(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
1655{
1656 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
1657 return;
1658
1659 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
1660
1661 if (target->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
1662 return;
1663
1664 // prepare spirit state
1665 if (apply)
1666 {
1667 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1668 {
1669 // disable breath/etc timers
1670 target->ToPlayer()->StopMirrorTimers();
1671
1672 // set stand state (expected in this form)
1673 if (!target->IsStandState())
1674 target->SetStandState(UNIT_STAND_STATE_STAND);
1675 }
1676
1677 target->SetHealth(1);
1678 }
1679 // die at aura end
1680 else if (target->IsAlive())
1681 // call functions which may have additional effects after chainging state of unit
1682 target->setDeathState(JUST_DIED);
1683}
1684
1685void AuraEffect::HandleAuraGhost(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
1686{
1687 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_SEND_FOR_CLIENT_MASK))
1688 return;
1689
1690 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
1691
1692 if (target->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
1693 return;
1694
1695 if (apply)
1696 {
1697 target->SetFlag(PLAYER_FLAGS, PLAYER_FLAGS_GHOST);
1698 target->m_serverSideVisibility.SetValue(SERVERSIDE_VISIBILITY_GHOST, GHOST_VISIBILITY_GHOST);
1699 target->m_serverSideVisibilityDetect.SetValue(SERVERSIDE_VISIBILITY_GHOST, GHOST_VISIBILITY_GHOST);
1700 }
1701 else
1702 {
1703 if (target->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_GHOST))
1704 return;
1705
1706 target->RemoveFlag(PLAYER_FLAGS, PLAYER_FLAGS_GHOST);
1707 target->m_serverSideVisibility.SetValue(SERVERSIDE_VISIBILITY_GHOST, GHOST_VISIBILITY_ALIVE);
1708 target->m_serverSideVisibilityDetect.SetValue(SERVERSIDE_VISIBILITY_GHOST, GHOST_VISIBILITY_ALIVE);
1709 }
1710}
1711
1712void AuraEffect::HandlePhase(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
1713{
1714 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
1715 return;
1716
1717 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
1718
1719 std::set<uint32> const& oldPhases = target->GetPhases();
1720 target->SetInPhase(GetMiscValueB(), false, apply);
1721
1722 // call functions which may have additional effects after chainging state of unit
1723 // phase auras normally not expected at BG but anyway better check
1724 if (apply)
1725 {
1726 // drop flag at invisibiliy in bg
1727 target->RemoveAurasWithInterruptFlags(AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_IMMUNE_OR_LOST_SELECTION);
1728 }
1729
1730 if (Player* player = target->ToPlayer())
1731 {
1732 if (player->IsInWorld())
1733 player->GetMap()->SendUpdateTransportVisibility(player, oldPhases);
1734 player->SendUpdatePhasing();
1735 }
1736
1737 // need triggering visibility update base at phase update of not GM invisible (other GMs anyway see in any phases)
1738 if (target->IsVisible())
1739 target->UpdateObjectVisibility();
1740}
1741
1742void AuraEffect::HandlePhaseGroup(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
1743{
1744 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
1745 return;
1746
1747 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
1748
1749 std::set<uint32> const& oldPhases = target->GetPhases();
1750 std::set<uint32> phases = sDB2Manager.GetPhasesForGroup(GetMiscValueB());
1751 for (auto phase : phases)
1752 target->SetInPhase(phase, false, apply);
1753
1754 // call functions which may have additional effects after chainging state of unit
1755 // phase auras normally not expected at BG but anyway better check
1756 if (apply)
1757 {
1758 // drop flag at invisibiliy in bg
1759 target->RemoveAurasWithInterruptFlags(AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_IMMUNE_OR_LOST_SELECTION);
1760 }
1761
1762 if (Player* player = target->ToPlayer())
1763 {
1764 if (player->IsInWorld())
1765 player->GetMap()->SendUpdateTransportVisibility(player, oldPhases);
1766 player->SendUpdatePhasing();
1767 }
1768
1769 // need triggering visibility update base at phase update of not GM invisible (other GMs anyway see in any phases)
1770 if (target->IsVisible())
1771 target->UpdateObjectVisibility();
1772}
1773
1774/**********************/
1775/*** UNIT MODEL ***/
1776/**********************/
1777
1778void AuraEffect::HandleAuraModShapeshift(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
1779{
1780 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
1781 return;
1782
1783 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
1784
1785 uint32 modelid = 0;
1786 Powers PowerType = POWER_MANA;
1787 ShapeshiftForm form = ShapeshiftForm(GetMiscValue());
1788
1789 switch (form)
1790 {
1791 case FORM_CAT: // 0x01
1792 case FORM_GHOUL: // 0x07
1793 PowerType = POWER_ENERGY;
1794 break;
1795
1796 case FORM_BEAR: // 0x05
1797
1798 case FORM_BATTLESTANCE: // 0x11
1799 case FORM_DEFENSIVESTANCE: // 0x12
1800 case FORM_BERSERKERSTANCE: // 0x13
1801 PowerType = POWER_RAGE;
1802 break;
1803
1804 case FORM_TREE: // 0x02
1805 case FORM_TRAVEL: // 0x03
1806 case FORM_AQUA: // 0x04
1807 case FORM_AMBIENT: // 0x06
1808
1809 case FORM_STEVES_GHOUL: // 0x09
1810 case FORM_THARONJA_SKELETON: // 0x0A
1811 case FORM_TEST_OF_STRENGTH: // 0x0B
1812 case FORM_BLB_PLAYER: // 0x0C
1813 case FORM_SHADOW_DANCE: // 0x0D
1814 case FORM_CREATUREBEAR: // 0x0E
1815 case FORM_CREATURECAT: // 0x0F
1816 case FORM_GHOSTWOLF: // 0x10
1817
1818 case FORM_TEST: // 0x14
1819 case FORM_ZOMBIE: // 0x15
1820 case FORM_METAMORPHOSIS: // 0x16
1821 case FORM_UNDEAD: // 0x19
1822 case FORM_MASTER_ANGLER: // 0x1A
1823 case FORM_FLIGHT_EPIC: // 0x1B
1824 case FORM_SHADOW: // 0x1C
1825 case FORM_FLIGHT: // 0x1D
1826 case FORM_STEALTH: // 0x1E
1827 case FORM_MOONKIN: // 0x1F
1828 case FORM_SPIRITOFREDEMPTION: // 0x20
1829 break;
1830 default:
1831 TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "Auras: Unknown Shapeshift Type: %u", GetMiscValue());
1832 }
1833
1834 modelid = target->GetModelForForm(form);
1835
1836 if (apply)
1837 {
1838 // remove polymorph before changing display id to keep new display id
1839 switch (form)
1840 {
1841 case FORM_CAT:
1842 case FORM_TREE:
1843 case FORM_TRAVEL:
1844 case FORM_AQUA:
1845 case FORM_BEAR:
1846 case FORM_FLIGHT_EPIC:
1847 case FORM_FLIGHT:
1848 case FORM_MOONKIN:
1849 {
1850 // remove movement affects
1851 target->RemoveMovementImpairingAuras();
1852
1853 // and polymorphic affects
1854 if (target->IsPolymorphed())
1855 target->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(target->getTransForm());
1856 break;
1857 }
1858 default:
1859 break;
1860 }
1861
1862 // remove other shapeshift before applying a new one
1863 target->RemoveAurasByType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_SHAPESHIFT, ObjectGuid::Empty, GetBase());
1864
1865 // stop handling the effect if it was removed by linked event
1866 if (aurApp->GetRemoveMode())
1867 return;
1868
1869 if (PowerType != POWER_MANA)
1870 {
1871 int32 oldPower = target->GetPower(PowerType);
1872 // reset power to default values only at power change
1873 if (target->getPowerType() != PowerType)
1874 target->setPowerType(PowerType);
1875
1876 if (form == FORM_CAT || form == FORM_BEAR)
1877 {
1878 // get furor proc chance
1879 int32 FurorChance = 0;
1880 if (AuraEffect const* dummy = target->GetDummyAuraEffect(SPELLFAMILY_DRUID, 238, 0))
1881 FurorChance = std::max(dummy->GetAmount(), 0);
1882
1883 if (form == FORM_CAT)
1884 {
1885 int32 basePoints = std::min<int32>(oldPower, FurorChance);
1886 target->SetPower(POWER_ENERGY, 0);
1887 target->CastCustomSpell(target, 17099, &basePoints, NULL, NULL, true, NULL, this);
1888 }
1889 else if (roll_chance_i(FurorChance))
1890 target->CastSpell(target, 17057, true);
1891 }
1892 }
1893 // stop handling the effect if it was removed by linked event
1894 if (aurApp->GetRemoveMode())
1895 return;
1896
1897 target->SetShapeshiftForm(form);
1898 if (modelid > 0)
1899 {
1900 SpellInfo const* transformSpellInfo = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(target->getTransForm());
1901 if (!transformSpellInfo || !GetSpellInfo()->IsPositive())
1902 target->SetDisplayId(modelid);
1903 }
1904 }
1905 else
1906 {
1907 // reset model id if no other auras present
1908 // may happen when aura is applied on linked event on aura removal
1909 if (!target->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_SHAPESHIFT))
1910 {
1911 target->SetShapeshiftForm(FORM_NONE);
1912 if (target->getClass() == CLASS_DRUID)
1913 {
1914 target->setPowerType(POWER_MANA);
1915 // Remove movement impairing effects also when shifting out
1916 target->RemoveMovementImpairingAuras();
1917 }
1918 }
1919
1920 if (modelid > 0)
1921 target->RestoreDisplayId();
1922
1923 switch (form)
1924 {
1925 // Nordrassil Harness - bonus
1926 case FORM_BEAR:
1927 case FORM_CAT:
1928 if (AuraEffect* dummy = target->GetAuraEffect(37315, 0))
1929 target->CastSpell(target, 37316, true, NULL, dummy);
1930 break;
1931 // Nordrassil Regalia - bonus
1932 case FORM_MOONKIN:
1933 if (AuraEffect* dummy = target->GetAuraEffect(37324, 0))
1934 target->CastSpell(target, 37325, true, NULL, dummy);
1935 break;
1936 case FORM_BATTLESTANCE:
1937 case FORM_DEFENSIVESTANCE:
1938 case FORM_BERSERKERSTANCE:
1939 {
1940 int32 Rage_val = 0;
1941 // Defensive Tactics
1942 if (form == FORM_DEFENSIVESTANCE)
1943 {
1944 if (AuraEffect const* aurEff = target->IsScriptOverriden(m_spellInfo, 831))
1945 Rage_val += aurEff->GetAmount() * 10;
1946 }
1947 // Stance mastery + Tactical mastery (both passive, and last have aura only in defense stance, but need apply at any stance switch)
1948 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1949 {
1950 PlayerSpellMap const& sp_list = target->ToPlayer()->GetSpellMap();
1951 for (PlayerSpellMap::const_iterator itr = sp_list.begin(); itr != sp_list.end(); ++itr)
1952 {
1953 if (itr->second->state == PLAYERSPELL_REMOVED || itr->second->disabled)
1954 continue;
1955
1956 SpellInfo const* spellInfo = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(itr->first);
1957 if (spellInfo && spellInfo->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_WARRIOR && spellInfo->SpellIconID == 139)
1958 Rage_val += target->CalculateSpellDamage(target, spellInfo, 0) * 10;
1959 }
1960 }
1961 if (target->GetPower(POWER_RAGE) > Rage_val)
1962 target->SetPower(POWER_RAGE, Rage_val);
1963 break;
1964 }
1965 default:
1966 break;
1967 }
1968 }
1969
1970 // adding/removing linked auras
1971 // add/remove the shapeshift aura's boosts
1972 HandleShapeshiftBoosts(target, apply);
1973
1974 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1975 target->ToPlayer()->InitDataForForm();
1976
1977 if (target->getClass() == CLASS_DRUID)
1978 {
1979 // Dash
1980 if (AuraEffect* aurEff = target->GetAuraEffect(SPELL_AURA_MOD_INCREASE_SPEED, SPELLFAMILY_DRUID, flag128(0, 0, 0x8)))
1981 aurEff->RecalculateAmount();
1982
1983 // Disarm handling
1984 // If druid shifts while being disarmed we need to deal with that since forms aren't affected by disarm
1985 // and also HandleAuraModDisarm is not triggered
1986 if (!target->CanUseAttackType(BASE_ATTACK))
1987 {
1988 if (Item* pItem = target->ToPlayer()->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, EQUIPMENT_SLOT_MAINHAND))
1989 target->ToPlayer()->_ApplyWeaponDamage(EQUIPMENT_SLOT_MAINHAND, pItem, apply);
1990 }
1991 }
1992
1993 // stop handling the effect if it was removed by linked event
1994 if (apply && aurApp->GetRemoveMode())
1995 return;
1996
1997 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1998 {
1999 SpellShapeshiftFormEntry const* shapeInfo = sSpellShapeshiftFormStore.LookupEntry(form);
2000 ASSERT(shapeInfo);
2001 // Learn spells for shapeshift form - no need to send action bars or add spells to spellbook
2002 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SHAPESHIFT_SPELLS; ++i)
2003 {
2004 if (!shapeInfo->PresetSpellID[i])
2005 continue;
2006 if (apply)
2007 target->ToPlayer()->AddTemporarySpell(shapeInfo->PresetSpellID[i]);
2008 else
2009 target->ToPlayer()->RemoveTemporarySpell(shapeInfo->PresetSpellID[i]);
2010 }
2011 }
2012}

2015{

2084 break;
2085 }
2086 // Murloc costume
2087 case 42365:
2088 target->SetDisplayId(21723);
2089 break;

2096 return;

2099 {
2100 // Blood Elf
2101 case RACE_BLOODELF:
2102 target->SetDisplayId(target->getGender() == GENDER_FEMALE ? 25043 : 25032);
2103 break;
2104 // Orc
2105 case RACE_ORC:
2106 target->SetDisplayId(target->getGender() == GENDER_FEMALE ? 25050 : 25039);
2107 break;

2111 break;

2115 break;

2119 break;

2123 break;

2131 break;

2135 break;
2136 // Night Elf
2137 case RACE_NIGHTELF:
2138 target->SetDisplayId(target->getGender() == GENDER_FEMALE ? 25038 : 25049);
2139 break;
2140 default:
2141 break;
2142 }
2143 break;
2144 }
2145 // Pygmy Oil
2146 case 53806:
2147 target->SetDisplayId(22512);
2148 break;
2149 // Honor the Dead
2150 case 65386:
2151 case 65495:
2152 target->SetDisplayId(target->getGender() == GENDER_MALE ? 29203 : 29204);
2153 break;
2154 // Darkspear Pride
2155 case 75532:
2156 target->SetDisplayId(target->getGender() == GENDER_MALE ? 31737 : 31738);
2157 break;
2158 // Gnomeregan Pride
2159 case 75531:
2160 target->SetDisplayId(target->getGender() == GENDER_MALE ? 31654 : 31655);
2161 break;
2162 default:
2163 break;
2164 }
2165 }
2166 else
2167 {
2168 CreatureTemplate const* ci = sObjectMgr->GetCreatureTemplate(GetMiscValue());
2169 if (!ci)
2170 {
2171 target->SetDisplayId(16358); // pig pink ^_^
2172 TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "Auras: unknown creature id = %d (only need its modelid) From Spell Aura Transform in Spell ID = %d", GetMiscValue(), GetId());
2173 }
2174 else
2175 {
2176 uint32 model_id = 0;
2177
2178 if (uint32 modelid = ci->GetRandomValidModelId())
2179 model_id = modelid; // Will use the default model here
2180
2181 target->SetDisplayId(model_id);
2182
2183 // Dragonmaw Illusion (set mount model also)
2184 if (GetId() == 42016 && target->GetMountID() && !target->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_INCREASE_MOUNTED_FLIGHT_SPEED).empty())
2185 target->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_FIELD_MOUNTDISPLAYID, 16314);
2186 }
2187 }
2188 }
2189
2190 // polymorph case
2191 if ((mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL) && target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && target->IsPolymorphed())
2192 {
2193 // for players, start regeneration after 1s (in polymorph fast regeneration case)
2194 // only if caster is Player (after patch 2.4.2)
2195 if (GetCasterGUID().IsPlayer())
2196 target->ToPlayer()->setRegenTimerCount(1*IN_MILLISECONDS);
2197
2198 //dismount polymorphed target (after patch 2.4.2)
2199 if (target->IsMounted())
2200 target->RemoveAurasByType(SPELL_AURA_MOUNTED);
2201 }
2202 }
2203 else
2204 {
2205 // HandleEffect(this, AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_SEND_FOR_CLIENT, true) will reapply it if need
2206 if (target->getTransForm() == GetId())
2207 target->setTransForm(0);
2208
2209 target->RestoreDisplayId();
2210
2211 // Dragonmaw Illusion (restore mount model)
2212 if (GetId() == 42016 && target->GetMountID() == 16314)
2213 {
2214 if (!target->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_MOUNTED).empty())
2215 {
2216 uint32 cr_id = target->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_MOUNTED).front()->GetMiscValue();
2217 if (CreatureTemplate const* ci = sObjectMgr->GetCreatureTemplate(cr_id))
2218 {
2219 uint32 displayID = ObjectMgr::ChooseDisplayId(ci);
2220 sObjectMgr->GetCreatureModelRandomGender(&displayID);
2221
2222 target->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_FIELD_MOUNTDISPLAYID, displayID);
2223 }
2224 }
2225 }
2226 }
2227}

2230{

2239}

2241void AuraEffect::HandleAuraCloneCaster(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
2242{
2243 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_SEND_FOR_CLIENT_MASK))
2244 return;
2245
2246 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
2247
2248 if (apply)
2249 {
2250 Unit* caster = GetCaster();
2251 if (!caster || caster == target)
2252 return;
2253
2254 // What must be cloned? at least display and scale
2255 target->SetDisplayId(caster->GetDisplayId());
2256 //target->SetObjectScale(caster->GetObjectScale()); // we need retail info about how scaling is handled (aura maybe?)
2257 target->SetFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS_2, UNIT_FLAG2_MIRROR_IMAGE);
2258 }
2259 else
2260 {
2261 target->SetDisplayId(target->GetNativeDisplayId());
2262 target->RemoveFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS_2, UNIT_FLAG2_MIRROR_IMAGE);
2263 }
2264}

2268/************************/
2269
2270void AuraEffect::HandleFeignDeath(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
2271{
2272 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
2273 return;
2274
2275 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
2276
2277 if (apply)
2278 {
2279 /*
2280 WorldPacket data(SMSG_FEIGN_DEATH_RESISTED, 0);
2281 target->SendMessageToSet(&data, true);
2282 */
2283
2284 UnitList targets;
2285 Trinity::AnyUnfriendlyUnitInObjectRangeCheck u_check(target, target, target->GetMap()->GetVisibilityRange());
2286 Trinity::UnitListSearcher<Trinity::AnyUnfriendlyUnitInObjectRangeCheck> searcher(target, targets, u_check);
2287 target->VisitNearbyObject(target->GetMap()->GetVisibilityRange(), searcher);
2288 for (UnitList::iterator iter = targets.begin(); iter != targets.end(); ++iter)
2289 {
2290 if (!(*iter)->HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_CASTING))
2291 continue;
2292
2293 for (uint32 i = CURRENT_FIRST_NON_MELEE_SPELL; i < CURRENT_MAX_SPELL; i++)
2294 {
2295 if ((*iter)->GetCurrentSpell(i)
2296 && (*iter)->GetCurrentSpell(i)->m_targets.GetUnitTargetGUID() == target->GetGUID())
2297 {
2298 (*iter)->InterruptSpell(CurrentSpellTypes(i), false);
2299 }
2300 }
2301 }
2302 target->CombatStop();
2303 target->RemoveAurasWithInterruptFlags(AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_IMMUNE_OR_LOST_SELECTION);
2304
2305 // prevent interrupt message
2306 if (GetCasterGUID() == target->GetGUID() && target->GetCurrentSpell(CURRENT_GENERIC_SPELL))
2307 target->FinishSpell(CURRENT_GENERIC_SPELL, false);
2308 target->InterruptNonMeleeSpells(true);
2309 target->getHostileRefManager().deleteReferences();
2310
2311 // stop handling the effect if it was removed by linked event
2312 if (aurApp->GetRemoveMode())
2313 return;
2314
2315 target->SetFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_UNK_29); // blizz like 2.0.x
2316 target->SetFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS_2, UNIT_FLAG2_FEIGN_DEATH); // blizz like 2.0.x
2317 target->SetFlag(OBJECT_DYNAMIC_FLAGS, UNIT_DYNFLAG_DEAD); // blizz like 2.0.x
2318 target->AddUnitState(UNIT_STATE_DIED);
2319
2320 if (Creature* creature = target->ToCreature())
2321 creature->SetReactState(REACT_PASSIVE);
2322 }
2323 else
2324 {
2325 /*
2326 WorldPacket data(SMSG_FEIGN_DEATH_RESISTED, 0);
2327 target->SendMessageToSet(&data, true);
2328 */
2329
2330 target->RemoveFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_UNK_29); // blizz like 2.0.x
2331 target->RemoveFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS_2, UNIT_FLAG2_FEIGN_DEATH); // blizz like 2.0.x
2332 target->RemoveFlag(OBJECT_DYNAMIC_FLAGS, UNIT_DYNFLAG_DEAD); // blizz like 2.0.x
2333 target->ClearUnitState(UNIT_STATE_DIED);
2334
2335 if (Creature* creature = target->ToCreature())
2336 creature->InitializeReactState();
2337 }
2338}
2339
2340void AuraEffect::HandleModUnattackable(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
2341{
2342 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_SEND_FOR_CLIENT_MASK))
2343 return;
2344
2345 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
2346
2347 // do not remove unit flag if there are more than this auraEffect of that kind on unit on unit
2348 if (!apply && target->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_UNATTACKABLE))
2349 return;
2350
2351 target->ApplyModFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_NON_ATTACKABLE, apply);
2352
2353 // call functions which may have additional effects after chainging state of unit
2354 if (apply && (mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
2355 {
2356 target->CombatStop();
2357 target->RemoveAurasWithInterruptFlags(AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_IMMUNE_OR_LOST_SELECTION);
2358 }
2359}
2360
2361void AuraEffect::HandleAuraModDisarm(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
2362{
2363 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
2364 return;
2365
2366 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
2367
2368 AuraType type = GetAuraType();
2369
2370 // Prevent handling aura twice
2371 if (apply ? target->GetAuraEffectsByType(type).size() > 1 : target->HasAuraType(type))
2372 return;
2373
2374 uint32 field, flag, slot;
2375 WeaponAttackType attType;
2376 switch (type)
2377 {
2378 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DISARM:
2379 field = UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS;
2380 flag = UNIT_FLAG_DISARMED;
2381 slot = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_MAINHAND;
2382 attType = BASE_ATTACK;
2383 break;
2384 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DISARM_OFFHAND:
2385 field = UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS_2;
2386 flag = UNIT_FLAG2_DISARM_OFFHAND;
2387 slot = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_OFFHAND;
2388 attType = OFF_ATTACK;
2389 break;
2390 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DISARM_RANGED:
2391 field = UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS_2;
2392 flag = UNIT_FLAG2_DISARM_RANGED;
2393 slot = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_MAINHAND;
2394 attType = RANGED_ATTACK;
2395 break;
2396 default:
2397 return;
2398 }
2399
2400 // if disarm aura is to be removed, remove the flag first to reapply damage/aura mods
2401 if (!apply)
2402 target->RemoveFlag(field, flag);
2403
2404 // Handle damage modification, shapeshifted druids are not affected
2405 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && !target->IsInFeralForm())
2406 {
2407 Player* player = target->ToPlayer();
2408 if (Item* item = player->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, slot))
2409 {
2410 uint8 attacktype = Player::GetAttackBySlot(slot, item->GetTemplate()->GetInventoryType());
2411
2412 if (attacktype < MAX_ATTACK)
2413 {
2414 player->_ApplyWeaponDamage(slot, item, !apply);
2415 player->_ApplyWeaponDependentAuraMods(item, WeaponAttackType(attacktype), !apply);
2416 }
2417 }
2418 }
2419
2420 // if disarm effects should be applied, wait to set flag until damage mods are unapplied
2421 if (apply)
2422 target->SetFlag(field, flag);
2423
2424 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT && target->ToCreature()->GetCurrentEquipmentId())
2425 target->UpdateDamagePhysical(attType);
2426}
2427
2428void AuraEffect::HandleAuraModSilence(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
2429{
2430 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
2431 return;
2432
2433 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
2434
2435 if (apply)
2436 {
2437 target->SetFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_SILENCED);
2438
2439 // call functions which may have additional effects after chainging state of unit
2440 // Stop cast only spells vs PreventionType == SPELL_PREVENTION_TYPE_SILENCE
2441 for (uint32 i = CURRENT_MELEE_SPELL; i < CURRENT_MAX_SPELL; ++i)
2442 if (Spell* spell = target->GetCurrentSpell(CurrentSpellTypes(i)))
2443 if (spell->m_spellInfo->PreventionType == SPELL_PREVENTION_TYPE_SILENCE)
2444 // Stop spells on prepare or casting state
2445 target->InterruptSpell(CurrentSpellTypes(i), false);
2446 }
2447 else
2448 {
2449 // do not remove unit flag if there are more than this auraEffect of that kind on unit on unit
2450 if (target->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_SILENCE) || target->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_PACIFY_SILENCE))
2451 return;
2452
2453 target->RemoveFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_SILENCED);
2454 }
2455}
2456
2457void AuraEffect::HandleAuraModPacify(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
2458{
2459 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_SEND_FOR_CLIENT_MASK))
2460 return;
2461
2462 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
2463
2464 if (apply)
2465 {
2466 target->SetFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_PACIFIED);
2467 target->AttackStop();
2468 }
2469 else
2470 {
2471 // do not remove unit flag if there are more than this auraEffect of that kind on unit on unit
2472 if (target->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_PACIFY) || target->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_PACIFY_SILENCE))
2473 return;
2474 target->RemoveFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_PACIFIED);
2475 }
2476}
2477
2478void AuraEffect::HandleAuraModPacifyAndSilence(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
2479{
2480 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_SEND_FOR_CLIENT_MASK))
2481 return;
2482
2483 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
2484
2485 // Vengeance of the Blue Flight (@todo REMOVE THIS!)
2486 /// @workaround
2487 if (m_spellInfo->Id == 45839)
2488 {
2489 if (apply)
2490 target->SetFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_NON_ATTACKABLE);
2491 else
2492 target->RemoveFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_NON_ATTACKABLE);
2493 }
2494 if (!(apply))
2495 {
2496 // do not remove unit flag if there are more than this auraEffect of that kind on unit on unit
2497 if (target->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_PACIFY_SILENCE))
2498 return;
2499 }
2500 HandleAuraModPacify(aurApp, mode, apply);
2501 HandleAuraModSilence(aurApp, mode, apply);
2502}

2504void AuraEffect::HandleAuraAllowOnlyAbility(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
2505{
2506 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_SEND_FOR_CLIENT_MASK))
2507 return;

2510
2511 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
2512 {
2513 if (apply)
2514 target->SetFlag(PLAYER_FLAGS, PLAYER_ALLOW_ONLY_ABILITY);
2515 else
2516 {
2517 // do not remove unit flag if there are more than this auraEffect of that kind on unit on unit
2518 if (target->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_ALLOW_ONLY_ABILITY))
2519 return;
2520 target->RemoveFlag(PLAYER_FLAGS, PLAYER_ALLOW_ONLY_ABILITY);
2521 }
2522 }
2523}

2638void AuraEffect::HandleAuraModSkill(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
2639{
2640 if (!(mode & (AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_MASK | AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_SKILL)))
2641 return;
2642
2643 Player* target = aurApp->GetTarget()->ToPlayer();
2644 if (!target)
2645 return;
2646
2647 uint32 prot = GetMiscValue();
2648 int32 points = GetAmount();
2649
2650 if (prot == SKILL_DEFENSE)
2651 return;
2652
2653 target->ModifySkillBonus(prot, (apply ? points : -points), GetAuraType() == SPELL_AURA_MOD_SKILL_TALENT);
2654}

2656/****************************/
2657/*** MOVEMENT ***/
2658/****************************/
2659
2660void AuraEffect::HandleAuraMounted(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
2661{
2662 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_SEND_FOR_CLIENT_MASK))
2663 return;
2664
2665 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
2666
2667 if (apply)
2668 {
2669 uint32 creatureEntry = GetMiscValue();
2670 uint32 displayId = 0;
2671 uint32 vehicleId = 0;
2672
2673 if (MountEntry const* mountEntry = sDB2Manager.GetMount(GetId()))
2674 {
2675 displayId = mountEntry->DisplayId;
2676 // TODO: CREATE TABLE mount_vehicle (mountId, vehicleCreatureId) for future mounts that are vehicles (new mounts no longer have proper data in MiscValue)
2677 //if (MountVehicle const* mountVehicle = sObjectMgr->GetMountVehicle(mountEntry->Id))
2678 // creatureEntry = mountVehicle->VehicleCreatureId;
2679 }
2680
2681 if (CreatureTemplate const* creatureInfo = sObjectMgr->GetCreatureTemplate(creatureEntry))
2682 {
2683 vehicleId = creatureInfo->VehicleId;
2684
2685 if (!displayId || vehicleId)
2686 {
2687 displayId = ObjectMgr::ChooseDisplayId(creatureInfo);
2688 sObjectMgr->GetCreatureModelRandomGender(&displayId);
2689 }
2690
2691 //some spell has one aura of mount and one of vehicle
2692 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetBase()->GetSpellEffectInfos())
2693 if (effect && effect->Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON && effect->MiscValue == GetMiscValue())
2694 displayId = 0;
2695 }
2696
2697 target->Mount(displayId, vehicleId, creatureEntry);
2698
2699 // cast speed aura
2700 if (mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL)
2701 if (MountCapabilityEntry const* mountCapability = sMountCapabilityStore.LookupEntry(GetAmount()))
2702 target->CastSpell(target, mountCapability->SpeedModSpell, true);
2703 }
2704 else
2705 {
2706 target->Dismount();
2707 //some mounts like Headless Horseman's Mount or broom stick are skill based spell
2708 // need to remove ALL arura related to mounts, this will stop client crash with broom stick
2709 // and never endless flying after using Headless Horseman's Mount
2710 if (mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL)
2711 {
2712 target->RemoveAurasByType(SPELL_AURA_MOUNTED);
2713
2714 // remove speed aura
2715 if (MountCapabilityEntry const* mountCapability = sMountCapabilityStore.LookupEntry(GetAmount()))
2716 target->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(mountCapability->SpeedModSpell, target->GetGUID());
2717 }
2718 }
2719}

2828/****************************/
2829
2830void AuraEffect::HandleModThreat(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
2831{
2832 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_MASK))
2833 return;
2834
2835 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
2836 for (int8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_SCHOOL; ++i)
2837 if (GetMiscValue() & (1 << i))
2838 ApplyPercentModFloatVar(target->m_threatModifier[i], float(GetAmount()), apply);
2839}

2842{

2844 return;

2846 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
2847
2848 if (!target->IsAlive() || target->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
2849 return;
2850
2851 Unit* caster = GetCaster();
2852 if (caster && caster->IsAlive())
2853 target->getHostileRefManager().addTempThreat((float)GetAmount(), apply);
2854}

2856void AuraEffect::HandleModTaunt(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
2857{
2858 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
2859 return;
2860

2862
2863 if (!target->IsAlive() || !target->CanHaveThreatList())
2864 return;
2865
2866 Unit* caster = GetCaster();
2867 if (!caster || !caster->IsAlive())
2868 return;
2869
2870 if (apply)
2871 target->TauntApply(caster);
2872 else
2873 {
2874 // When taunt aura fades out, mob will switch to previous target if current has less than 1.1 * secondthreat
2875 target->TauntFadeOut(caster);
2876 }
2877}

2938/***************************/
2939/*** CHARM ***/
2940/***************************/
2941
2942void AuraEffect::HandleModPossess(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
2943{
2944 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
2945 return;
2946
2947 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
2948
2949 Unit* caster = GetCaster();
2950
2951 // no support for posession AI yet
2952 if (caster && caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT)
2953 {
2954 HandleModCharm(aurApp, mode, apply);
2955 return;
2956 }
2957
2958 if (apply)
2959 target->SetCharmedBy(caster, CHARM_TYPE_POSSESS, aurApp);
2960 else
2961 target->RemoveCharmedBy(caster);
2962}
2963
2964void AuraEffect::HandleModPossessPet(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
2965{
2966 // Used by spell "Eyes of the Beast"
2967
2968 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
2969 return;
2970
2971 Unit* caster = GetCaster();
2972 if (!caster || caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
2973 return;
2974
2975 //seems it may happen that when removing it is no longer owner's pet
2976 //if (caster->ToPlayer()->GetPet() != target)
2977 // return;
2978
2979 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
2980 if (target->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_UNIT || !target->IsPet())
2981 return;
2982
2983 Pet* pet = target->ToPet();
2984
2985 if (apply)
2986 {
2987 if (caster->ToPlayer()->GetPet() != pet)
2988 return;
2989
2990 // Must clear current motion or pet leashes back to owner after a few yards
2991 // when under spell 'Eyes of the Beast'
2992 pet->GetMotionMaster()->Clear();
2993 pet->SetCharmedBy(caster, CHARM_TYPE_POSSESS, aurApp);
2994 }
2995 else
2996 {
2997 pet->RemoveCharmedBy(caster);
2998
2999 if (!pet->IsWithinDistInMap(caster, pet->GetMap()->GetVisibilityRange()))
3000 pet->Remove(PET_SAVE_NOT_IN_SLOT, true);
3001 else
3002 {
3003 // Reinitialize the pet bar or it will appear greyed out
3004 caster->ToPlayer()->PetSpellInitialize();
3005
3006 // Follow owner only if not fighting or owner didn't click "stay" at new location
3007 // This may be confusing because pet bar shows "stay" when under the spell but it retains
3008 // the "follow" flag. Player MUST click "stay" while under the spell.
3009 if (!pet->GetVictim() && !pet->GetCharmInfo()->HasCommandState(COMMAND_STAY))
3010 {
3011 pet->GetMotionMaster()->MoveFollow(caster, PET_FOLLOW_DIST, pet->GetFollowAngle());
3012 }
3013 }
3014 }
3015}
3016
3017void AuraEffect::HandleModCharm(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
3018{
3019 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
3020 return;
3021
3022 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
3023
3024 Unit* caster = GetCaster();
3025
3026 if (apply)
3027 target->SetCharmedBy(caster, CHARM_TYPE_CHARM, aurApp);
3028 else
3029 target->RemoveCharmedBy(caster);
3030}

3047/**
3048 * Such auras are applied from a caster(=player) to a vehicle.
3049 * This has been verified using spell #49256
3050 */
3051void AuraEffect::HandleAuraControlVehicle(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
3052{
3053 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_MASK))
3054 return;
3055
3056 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
3057 if (!target->IsVehicle())
3058 return;
3059
3060 Unit* caster = GetCaster();
3061 if (!caster || caster == target)
3062 return;
3063
3064 if (apply)
3065 {
3066 // Currently spells that have base points 0 and DieSides 0 = "0/0" exception are pushed to -1,
3067 // however the idea of 0/0 is to ingore flag VEHICLE_SEAT_FLAG_CAN_ENTER_OR_EXIT and -1 checks for it,
3068 // so this break such spells or most of them.
3069 // Current formula about m_amount: effect base points + dieside - 1
3070 // TO DO: Reasearch more about 0/0 and fix it.
3071 caster->_EnterVehicle(target->GetVehicleKit(), m_amount - 1, aurApp);
3072 }
3073 else
3074 {
3075 // Remove pending passengers before exiting vehicle - might cause an Uninstall
3076 target->GetVehicleKit()->RemovePendingEventsForPassenger(caster);
3077
3078 if (GetId() == 53111) // Devour Humanoid
3079 {
3080 target->Kill(caster);
3081 if (caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT)
3082 caster->ToCreature()->RemoveCorpse();
3083 }
3084
3085 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT))
3086 caster->_ExitVehicle();
3087 else
3088 target->GetVehicleKit()->RemovePassenger(caster); // Only remove passenger from vehicle without launching exit movement or despawning the vehicle
3089
3090 // some SPELL_AURA_CONTROL_VEHICLE auras have a dummy effect on the player - remove them
3091 caster->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(GetId());
3092 }
3093}

3108void AuraEffect::HandleAuraModIncreaseMountedSpeed(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const

3110 HandleAuraModIncreaseSpeed(aurApp, mode, apply);

3112
3113void AuraEffect::HandleAuraModIncreaseFlightSpeed(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
3114{
3115 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_SEND_FOR_CLIENT_MASK))
3116 return;
3117
3118 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
3119 if (mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_MASK)
3120 target->UpdateSpeed(MOVE_FLIGHT, true);
3121
3122 //! Update ability to fly
3123 if (GetAuraType() == SPELL_AURA_MOD_INCREASE_MOUNTED_FLIGHT_SPEED)
3124 {
3125 // do not remove unit flag if there are more than this auraEffect of that kind on unit on unit
3126 if (mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_SEND_FOR_CLIENT_MASK && (apply || (!target->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_INCREASE_MOUNTED_FLIGHT_SPEED) && !target->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_FLY))))
3127 {
3128 target->SetCanFly(apply);
3129
3130 if (!apply && target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT && !target->IsLevitating())
3131 target->GetMotionMaster()->MoveFall();
3132 }
3133
3134 //! Someone should clean up these hacks and remove it from this function. It doesn't even belong here.
3135 if (mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL)
3136 {
3137 //Players on flying mounts must be immune to polymorph
3138 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
3139 target->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_MECHANIC, MECHANIC_POLYMORPH, apply);
3140
3141 // Dragonmaw Illusion (overwrite mount model, mounted aura already applied)
3142 if (apply && target->HasAuraEffect(42016, 0) && target->GetMountID())
3143 target->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_FIELD_MOUNTDISPLAYID, 16314);
3144 }
3145 }
3146}
3147
3148void AuraEffect::HandleAuraModIncreaseSwimSpeed(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool /*apply*/) const
3149{
3150 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_MASK))
3151 return;
3152
3153 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
3154
3155 target->UpdateSpeed(MOVE_SWIM, true);
3156}
3157
3158void AuraEffect::HandleAuraModDecreaseSpeed(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool /*apply*/) const
3159{
3160 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_MASK))
3161 return;
3162
3163 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
3164
3165 target->UpdateSpeed(MOVE_RUN, true);
3166 target->UpdateSpeed(MOVE_SWIM, true);
3167 target->UpdateSpeed(MOVE_FLIGHT, true);
3168 target->UpdateSpeed(MOVE_RUN_BACK, true);
3169 target->UpdateSpeed(MOVE_SWIM_BACK, true);
3170 target->UpdateSpeed(MOVE_FLIGHT_BACK, true);
3171}
3172
3173void AuraEffect::HandleAuraModUseNormalSpeed(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool /*apply*/) const
3174{
3175 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
3176 return;
3177
3178 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
3179
3180 target->UpdateSpeed(MOVE_RUN, true);
3181 target->UpdateSpeed(MOVE_SWIM, true);
3182 target->UpdateSpeed(MOVE_FLIGHT, true);
3183}

3406 if (miscVal & (1<<1))
3407 aura_immunity_list.push_back(SPELL_AURA_TRANSFORM);
3408
3409 // These flag can be recognized wrong:
3410 if (miscVal & (1<<6))
3411 aura_immunity_list.push_back(SPELL_AURA_MOD_DECREASE_SPEED);
3412 if (miscVal & (1<<0))
3413 aura_immunity_list.push_back(SPELL_AURA_MOD_ROOT);
3414 if (miscVal & (1<<2))
3415 aura_immunity_list.push_back(SPELL_AURA_MOD_CONFUSE);
3416 if (miscVal & (1<<9))
3417 aura_immunity_list.push_back(SPELL_AURA_MOD_FEAR);
3418 if (miscVal & (1<<7))
3419 aura_immunity_list.push_back(SPELL_AURA_MOD_DISARM);
3420 }
3421
3422 // apply immunities
3423 for (std::list <AuraType>::iterator iter = aura_immunity_list.begin(); iter != aura_immunity_list.end(); ++iter)
3424 target->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_STATE, *iter, apply);
3425
3426 if (apply && GetSpellInfo()->AttributesEx & SPELL_ATTR1_DISPEL_AURAS_ON_IMMUNITY)
3427 {
3428 target->RemoveAurasWithMechanic(mechanic_immunity_list, AURA_REMOVE_BY_DEFAULT, GetId());
3429 for (std::list <AuraType>::iterator iter = aura_immunity_list.begin(); iter != aura_immunity_list.end(); ++iter)
3430 target->RemoveAurasByType(*iter);
3431 }
3432}
3433
3434void AuraEffect::HandleModMechanicImmunity(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
3435{
3436 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
3437 return;
3438
3439 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
3440 uint32 mechanic;
3441
3442 switch (GetId())
3443 {
3444 case 34471: // The Beast Within
3445 case 19574: // Bestial Wrath
3446 mechanic = IMMUNE_TO_MOVEMENT_IMPAIRMENT_AND_LOSS_CONTROL_MASK;
3447 target->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_MECHANIC, MECHANIC_CHARM, apply);
3448 target->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_MECHANIC, MECHANIC_DISORIENTED, apply);
3449 target->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_MECHANIC, MECHANIC_FEAR, apply);
3450 target->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_MECHANIC, MECHANIC_ROOT, apply);
3451 target->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_MECHANIC, MECHANIC_SLEEP, apply);
3452 target->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_MECHANIC, MECHANIC_SNARE, apply);
3453 target->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_MECHANIC, MECHANIC_STUN, apply);
3454 target->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_MECHANIC, MECHANIC_FREEZE, apply);
3455 target->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_MECHANIC, MECHANIC_KNOCKOUT, apply);
3456 target->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_MECHANIC, MECHANIC_POLYMORPH, apply);
3457 target->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_MECHANIC, MECHANIC_BANISH, apply);
3458 target->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_MECHANIC, MECHANIC_SHACKLE, apply);
3459 target->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_MECHANIC, MECHANIC_TURN, apply);
3460 target->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_MECHANIC, MECHANIC_HORROR, apply);
3461 target->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_MECHANIC, MECHANIC_DAZE, apply);
3462 target->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_MECHANIC, MECHANIC_SAPPED, apply);
3463 break;
3464 case 42292: // PvP trinket
3465 case 59752: // Every Man for Himself
3466 mechanic = IMMUNE_TO_MOVEMENT_IMPAIRMENT_AND_LOSS_CONTROL_MASK;
3467 // Actually we should apply immunities here, too, but the aura has only 100 ms duration, so there is practically no point
3468 break;
3469 case 54508: // Demonic Empowerment
3470 mechanic = (1 << MECHANIC_SNARE) | (1 << MECHANIC_ROOT);
3471 target->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_MECHANIC, MECHANIC_SNARE, apply);
3472 target->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_MECHANIC, MECHANIC_ROOT, apply);
3473 target->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_MECHANIC, MECHANIC_STUN, apply);
3474 break;
3475 default:
3476 if (GetMiscValue() < 1)
3477 return;
3478 mechanic = 1 << GetMiscValue();
3479 target->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_MECHANIC, GetMiscValue(), apply);
3480 break;
3481 }
3482
3483 if (apply && GetSpellInfo()->AttributesEx & SPELL_ATTR1_DISPEL_AURAS_ON_IMMUNITY)
3484 target->RemoveAurasWithMechanic(mechanic, AURA_REMOVE_BY_DEFAULT, GetId());
3485}
3486
3487void AuraEffect::HandleAuraModEffectImmunity(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
3488{
3489 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
3490 return;
3491
3492 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
3493
3494 target->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_EFFECT, GetMiscValue(), apply);
3495
3496 // when removing flag aura, handle flag drop
3497 Player* player = target->ToPlayer();
3498 if (!apply && player && (GetSpellInfo()->AuraInterruptFlags & AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_IMMUNE_OR_LOST_SELECTION))
3499 {
3500 if (player->InBattleground())
3501 {
3502 if (Battleground* bg = player->GetBattleground())
3503 bg->EventPlayerDroppedFlag(player);
3504 }
3505 else
3506 sOutdoorPvPMgr->HandleDropFlag(player, GetSpellInfo()->Id);
3507 }
3508}
3509
3510void AuraEffect::HandleAuraModStateImmunity(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
3511{
3512 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
3513 return;
3514
3515 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
3516
3517 target->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_STATE, GetMiscValue(), apply);
3518
3519 if (apply && GetSpellInfo()->AttributesEx & SPELL_ATTR1_DISPEL_AURAS_ON_IMMUNITY)
3520 target->RemoveAurasByType(AuraType(GetMiscValue()), ObjectGuid::Empty, GetBase());
3521}
3522
3523void AuraEffect::HandleAuraModSchoolImmunity(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
3524{
3525 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
3526 return;
3527
3528 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
3529
3530 target->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_SCHOOL, GetMiscValue(), (apply));
3531
3532 if (GetSpellInfo()->Mechanic == MECHANIC_BANISH)
3533 {
3534 if (apply)
3535 target->AddUnitState(UNIT_STATE_ISOLATED);
3536 else
3537 {
3538 bool banishFound = false;
3539 Unit::AuraEffectList const& banishAuras = target->GetAuraEffectsByType(GetAuraType());
3540 for (Unit::AuraEffectList::const_iterator i = banishAuras.begin(); i != banishAuras.end(); ++i)
3541 if ((*i)->GetSpellInfo()->Mechanic == MECHANIC_BANISH)
3542 {
3543 banishFound = true;
3544 break;
3545 }
3546 if (!banishFound)
3547 target->ClearUnitState(UNIT_STATE_ISOLATED);
3548 }
3549 }
3550
3551 if (apply && GetMiscValue() == SPELL_SCHOOL_MASK_NORMAL)
3552 target->RemoveAurasWithInterruptFlags(AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_IMMUNE_OR_LOST_SELECTION);
3553
3554 // remove all flag auras (they are positive, but they must be removed when you are immune)
3555 if (GetSpellInfo()->AttributesEx & SPELL_ATTR1_DISPEL_AURAS_ON_IMMUNITY
3556 && GetSpellInfo()->AttributesEx2 & SPELL_ATTR2_DAMAGE_REDUCED_SHIELD)
3557 target->RemoveAurasWithInterruptFlags(AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_IMMUNE_OR_LOST_SELECTION);
3558
3559 /// @todo optimalize this cycle - use RemoveAurasWithInterruptFlags call or something else
3560 if ((apply)
3561 && GetSpellInfo()->AttributesEx & SPELL_ATTR1_DISPEL_AURAS_ON_IMMUNITY
3562 && GetSpellInfo()->IsPositive()) //Only positive immunity removes auras
3563 {
3564 uint32 school_mask = GetMiscValue();
3565 Unit::AuraApplicationMap& Auras = target->GetAppliedAuras();
3566 for (Unit::AuraApplicationMap::iterator iter = Auras.begin(); iter != Auras.end();)
3567 {
3568 SpellInfo const* spell = iter->second->GetBase()->GetSpellInfo();
3569 if ((spell->GetSchoolMask() & school_mask)//Check for school mask
3570 && GetSpellInfo()->CanDispelAura(spell)
3571 && !iter->second->IsPositive() //Don't remove positive spells
3572 && spell->Id != GetId()) //Don't remove self
3573 {
3574 target->RemoveAura(iter);
3575 }
3576 else
3577 ++iter;
3578 }
3579 }
3580}
3581
3582void AuraEffect::HandleAuraModDmgImmunity(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
3583{
3584 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
3585 return;
3586
3587 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
3588
3589 target->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_DAMAGE, GetMiscValue(), apply);
3590}

3600}
